<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 15 at 5:39AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FOG DEVELOPING AND PERSISTING...
Surface observations within the Rio Grande Valley and across all
of Deep South Texas indicate that patchy fog is developing and
persisting due to the combination of light winds, clear skies, and
a moist atmosphere. The fog will generally reduce the visibility
to between 2 and 4 miles, with isolated patches of more dense fog
reducing visibilities to one half of a mile or less.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and
avoid following other cars too closely in any fog during the next
few hours.</description>
